Halve and peel the @onion{1/2%unit}. Chop half into small pieces.

Zest half the @lemon{1/2%unit} then cut in half. Roughly chop the @parsley{5%g} (stalks and all).

Trim the @carrot{2%unit} and slice into 1cm rounds (no need to peel).

Quarter the @cherry tomatoes{125%g}.

Mix @oil{1%tbsp}, the lemon zest, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} in a #large bowl{}. Add the @hake{250%g}. Turn to coat well and set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Place a #medium pot{} over medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the chopped onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @water{240%ml}, then stir in the @vegetable stock{1%sachet} and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Cover and remove from heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Place a #large pan{} over a medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the carrot rounds and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes} each side.

Turn only every so often—this will allow the carrot to pick up a nice colour.

Once cooked, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}, then transfer half the charred carrot to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Chop the remaining carrot into small pieces and set aside.

Meanwhile, to a #medium bowl{} add @oil{1 1/2%tbsp} and a squeeze of lemon juice.

Add half the chopped parsley.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Mix well and set aside.

Return the (now empty) pan to medium-high heat.

Once hot, carefully place your marinated hake into the pan.

Spoon over any marinade remaining in the bowl.

Cook for ~{3-4%minutes} before turning over and cooking for ~{2-3%minutes} on the other side.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

When everything is ready, fluff up the bulgur with a #fork{} and stir through the tomatoes, chopped carrots, remaining parsley and a small squeeze of lemon juice.

Taste then season with salt, pepper and more lemon juice if desired.

Share the bulgur between your plates, then top with the charred carrot rounds and crispy hake.

Drizzle over the herby dressing to finish.